{{ThisDateInRecentYears}} 
{{Day}}

==Events==
*[[3114 BC]] &amp;ndash; The [[Mesoamerican Long Count calendar]], used by several [[pre-Columbian]] [[Mesoamerica]]n civilizations, notably the [[Mayan Civilization|Mayans]], begins.
*[[2492 BC]] &amp;ndash; Traditional date of the defeat of [[Bel (mythology)|Bel]] by [[Hayk]], progenitor and founder of the [[Armenians|Armenian]] nation.
* [[355]] &amp;ndash; [[Claudius Silvanus]], accused of treason, proclaims himself [[Roman Emperor]] against [[Constantius II]].
*[[1755]] &amp;ndash; [[Charles Lawrence (British Army officer)|Charles Lawrence]] gives expulsion orders to remove the [[Acadians]] from [[Nova Scotia]] beginning the [[Great Upheaval]].
*[[1786]] &amp;ndash; Captain [[Francis Light]] establishes the British colony of [[Penang]] in [[Malaysia]]
*[[1804]] &amp;ndash; [[Francis II, Holy Roman Emperor|Francis II]] assumes the title of first [[Emperor of Austria]].
*[[1858]] &amp;ndash; The [[Eiger]] in the [[Bernese Alps]] is ascended for the first time by [[Charles Barrington (mountaineer)|Charles Barrington]] accompanied by [[Christian Almer]] and Peter Bohren.
*[[1898]] &amp;ndash; [[Spanish-American War]]: American troops enter the city of [[Mayagüez, Puerto Rico|Mayagüez]], [[Puerto Rico]].
*[[1918]] &amp;ndash; [[World War I]]: the [[Battle of Amiens (1918)|Battle of Amiens]] ends.
*[[1919]] &amp;ndash; The [[Weimar Constitution|constitution]] of the [[Weimar Republic]] is adopted.
*[[1920]] &amp;ndash; The [[Latvia]]-[[Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic|Bolshevist Russia]] peace treaty, which relinquished Russia's authority and pretenses to Latvia, is signed.
*[[1929]] &amp;ndash; [[Babe Ruth]] becomes the first [[baseball]] player to hit [[500 home run club|500]] [[home run]]s in his career with a home run at [[League Park]] in [[Cleveland, Ohio]].
*[[1934]] &amp;ndash; The first civilian prisoners arrive at the Federal prison on [[Alcatraz Island]].
*[[1942]] &amp;ndash; Actress [[Hedy Lamarr]] and composer [[George Antheil]] receive a patent for a [[frequency hopping]], [[spread spectrum]] communication system that later became the basis for modern technologies in wireless telephones and [[Wi-Fi]].
*[[1952]] &amp;ndash; [[King Hussein|Hussein]] is proclaimed King of [[Jordan]].
*[[1960]] &amp;ndash; [[Chad]] declares independence.
*[[1965]] &amp;ndash; Race riots (the [[Watts riots]]) begin in the [[Watts, Los Angeles, California|Watts]] area of [[Los Angeles, California]].
*[[1972]] &amp;ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: the last [[United States]] ground combat unit departs [[South Vietnam]].
*[[1975]] &amp;ndash; [[East Timor]]: Governor [[Mário Lemos Pires]] of [[Portuguese Timor]] abandons the capital [[Dili]], following a coup by the [[Timorese Democratic Union]] (UDT) and the outbreak of civil war between UDT and [[Fretilin]].
*[[1982]] &amp;ndash; A bomb explodes on [[Pan Am Flight 830]], ''en route'' from [[Tokyo]] to [[Honolulu]], killing one teenager and injuring 15 passengers.
*[[1999]] &amp;ndash; The [[Salt Lake City Tornado]] tears through the downtown district of the city, killing one.
*[[2003]] &amp;ndash; [[NATO]] takes over command of the [[International Security Assistance Force|peacekeeping force]] in [[Afghanistan]], marking its first major operation outside [[Europe]] in its 54-year-history.
*  2003   &amp;ndash; [[Jemaah Islamiyah]] leader [[Riduan Isamuddin]], better known as Hambali, is arrested in [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]].
*  2003   &amp;ndash; A [[heat wave]] in [[Paris]] results in temperatures rising to {{Convert|112|°F|°C}}, leaving about 144 people dead.

