*  1996   &amp;ndash; [[Mel Taylor]], American drummer ([[The Ventures]]) (b. 1933)
*  1996   &amp;ndash; [[Baba Vanga]], Macedonian-born Bulgarian prophet, mystic, clairvoyant and herbalist (b. 1911)
*[[2000]] &amp;ndash; [[Jean Papineau-Couture]], Canadian composer (b. 1916)
*[[2001]] &amp;ndash; [[Percy Stallard]], English cyclist (b. 1909)
*[[2002]] &amp;ndash; [[Galen Rowell]], American photographer and mountain climber (b. 1940)
*[[2003]] &amp;ndash; [[Armand Borel]], Swiss mathematician (b. 1923)
*  2003   &amp;ndash; [[Herb Brooks]], American ice hockey coach (b. 1937)
*[[2005]] &amp;ndash; [[James Booth]], English actor (b. 1927)
*[[2006]] &amp;ndash; [[Mike Douglas]], American singer and talk show host (b. 1925)
*[[2009]] &amp;ndash; [[Eunice Kennedy Shriver]], American founder of the [[Special Olympics]], sister of [[John F. Kennedy]] (b. 1921)
*[[2010]] &amp;ndash; [[Markus Liebherr]], German-born Swiss owner of Southampton Football Club (b. 1948)
