*[[1923]] &amp;ndash; [[George Herbert, 5th Earl of Carnarvon]], English financier (b. 1866)
*[[1928]] &amp;ndash; [[Roy Kilner]], English cricketer (b. 1890)
*[[1932]] &amp;ndash; [[Phar Lap]], Australian Racehorse (b. 1926)
*[[1941]] &amp;ndash; [[Sir Nigel Gresley]], Steam locomotive engineer (b. 1876)
*[[1943]] &amp;ndash; [[Aleš Hrdlička]], Czech anthropologist (b. 1869)
*[[1945]] &amp;ndash; [[Karl Otto Koch]], German SS-officer (b. 1897)
*  1945   &amp;ndash; [[Huldreich Georg Früh]], Swiss composer (b. 1903)
*[[1946]] &amp;ndash; [[Vincent Youmans]], American songwriter (b. 1898)
*[[1952]] &amp;ndash; [[Charles Collett]], [[Great Western Railway|GWR]] chief mechanical engineer (b. 1871)
*[[1964]] &amp;ndash; [[Douglas MacArthur]], American [[general]] (b. 1880)
*[[1967]] &amp;ndash; [[Hermann Joseph Muller]], American geneticist, [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine|Nobel laureate]] (b. 1890)
*  1967   &amp;ndash; [[Mischa Elman]], Ukrainian violinist (b. 1891)
*[[1969]] &amp;ndash; [[Ain-Ervin Mere]], Estonian Nazi (b. 1903)
*  1969   &amp;ndash; [[Shelby Storck]], American television producer (b. 1917)
*[[1970]] &amp;ndash; [[Alfred Henry Sturtevant]], American geneticist (b. 1891)
*[[1972]] &amp;ndash; [[Brian Donlevy]], American actor (b. 1901)
*  1972   &amp;ndash; [[Isabel Jewell]], American actress (b. 1907)
*[[1973]] &amp;ndash; [[John Coleman (Australian footballer)|John Coleman]], Australian rules footballer (b. 1928)
*[[1974]] &amp;ndash; [[A. Y. Jackson]], Canadian painter (b. 1882)
*[[1975]] &amp;ndash; [[Chiang Kai-shek]], 1st President of the Republic of China (b. 1887)
*[[1976]] &amp;ndash; [[Howard Hughes]], American aviator (b. 1905)
*  1976   &amp;ndash; [[Wilder Penfield]], Canadian surgeon (b. 1891)
*[[1979]] &amp;ndash; [[Eugène Gabritschevsky]], Russian biologist and artist (b. 1893)
*[[1981]] &amp;ndash; [[Bob Hite]], American singer ([[Canned Heat]]) (b. 1945)
*[[1982]] &amp;ndash; [[Abe Fortas]], U.S. Supreme Court Justice (b. 1910)
*[[1983]] &amp;ndash; [[Danny Rapp]], American musician ([[Danny &amp; the Juniors]]) (b. 1941)
*[[1987]] &amp;ndash; [[Jan Lindblad]], Swedish naturalist, writer, photographer (b. 1932)
*[[1989]] &amp;ndash; [[María Cristina Gómez]], Salvadoran Teacher (b. 1938)
*[[1991]] &amp;ndash; [[John Tower]], American politician (b. 1925)
*  1991   &amp;ndash; [[Sonny Carter]], American astronaut (b. 1947)
*  1992   &amp;ndash; [[Sam Walton]], American retailer (b. 1918)
*[[1993]] &amp;ndash; [[Divya Bharti]], Indian Bollywood actress (b. 1974)
*[[1994]] &amp;ndash; [[Kurt Cobain]], musician ([[Nirvana (band)|Nirvana]]) (b. 1967)
*[[1997]] &amp;ndash; [[Allen Ginsberg]], American poet (b. 1926)
*[[1998]] &amp;ndash; [[Cozy Powell]], British musician (b. 1947)
*[[1999]] &amp;ndash; [[Paul David]], French-Canadian cardiologist (b. 1919)
*[[2000]] &amp;ndash; [[Lee Petty]], American race car driver (b. 1914)
*[[2001]] &amp;ndash; [[Brother Theodore]], German comedian (b. 1906)
*[[2002]] &amp;ndash; [[Layne Staley]], American musician ([[Alice in Chains]]) (b. 1967)
*[[2004]] &amp;ndash; [[Heiner Zieschang]], German mathematician (b. 1936)
*  2004   &amp;ndash; [[Sławomir Rawicz]], Polish soldier (b. 1915)
*[[2005]] &amp;ndash; [[Saul Bellow]], Canadian born writer, [[Nobel Prize in Literature|Nobel laureate]] (b. 1915)
*  2005   &amp;ndash; [[Dale Messick]], American comic strip artist (b. 1906)
*  2005   &amp;ndash; [[Debralee Scott]], American actress (b. 1953)
*  2005   &amp;ndash; [[John Sichel]], British film and television director (b. 1937)
*[[2006]] &amp;ndash; [[Gene Pitney]], American singer (b. 1941)
*[[2007]] &amp;ndash; [[Mark St. John]], American musician ([[Kiss (band)|Kiss]]) (b. 1956)
*  2007   &amp;ndash; [[Darryl Stingley]], American football player (b. 1951)
*  2007   &amp;ndash; [[Maria Gripe]], Swedish writer (b. 1923)
*  2007   &amp;ndash; [[Leela Majumdar]], Bengali writer (b. 1908)
*  2007   &amp;ndash; [[Poornachandra Tejaswi]], Kannada writer (b. 1938)
*[[2008]] &amp;ndash; [[Charlton Heston]], American actor (b. 1923)
*[[2009]] &amp;ndash; [[Constantine Papadakis]], Greek-American businessman (b. 1946)
