If there are multiple people in the same birth year, put them in alphabetical order of surname.
Do not trust &quot;this year in history&quot; websites for accurate date information. --&gt;

==Deaths==
*[[1176]] &amp;ndash; [[Richard de Clare, 2nd Earl of Pembroke]], English military leader (b. 1130)
*[[1314]] &amp;ndash; [[Pope Clement V]] (b. 1264)
*[[1521]] &amp;ndash; [[Zhengde]], Emperor of China (b. 1491)
*[[1534]] &amp;ndash; [[Elizabeth Barton]], English nun (executed)
*[[1558]] &amp;ndash; [[Johannes Bugenhagen]], German reformer (b. 1485)
*[[1643]] &amp;ndash; [[Christoph Demantius]], German composer (b. 1567)
*[[1703]] &amp;ndash; [[Lancelot Addison]], English royal chaplain (b. 1632)
*[[1769]] &amp;ndash; [[Chief Pontiac|Pontiac]], Chief of the Ottawa (b. 1720)
*[[1831]] &amp;ndash; [[John Abernethy (surgeon)|John Abernethy]], English surgeon (b. 1764)
*[[1873]] &amp;ndash; [[William Tite]], English architect (b. 1798)
*[[1874]] &amp;ndash; [[Alexander H. Bailey]], American politician (b. 1817)
*[[1887]] &amp;ndash; [[Muhammad Sharif Pasha]], Egyptian statesman (b. 1826)
*[[1899]] &amp;ndash; [[Joseph Wolf]], German artist (b. 1820)
*[[1902]] &amp;ndash; [[Joaquim de Sousa Andrade]], Brazilian poet who designed the [[Maranhão#Flag|flag of the State of Maranhão]] (b. 1833)
*[[1912]] &amp;ndash; [[Bram Stoker]], Irish author (b. 1847)
*[[1918]] &amp;ndash; [[Karl Ferdinand Braun]], German physicist, [[Nobel Prize in Physics|Nobel Prize]] laureate (b. 1850)
*[[1929]] &amp;ndash; [[Prince Albert Wilhelm Heinrich of Prussia]] (b. 1862)
*[[1932]] &amp;ndash; [[Giuseppe Peano]], Italian mathematician (b. 1858)
*[[1944]] &amp;ndash; [[Elmer Gedeon]], one of two [[Major League Baseball]] fatal casualties during [[World War II]].
*[[1945]] &amp;ndash; [[Erwin Bumke]], German jurist (b. 1874)
*[[1947]] &amp;ndash; King [[Christian X of Denmark]] (b. 1870)
*[[1951]] &amp;ndash; [[Ivanoe Bonomi]], [[Prime Minister of Italy]] (b. 1873)
*[[1964]] &amp;ndash; [[Eddie Dyer]], American baseball player (b. 1899)
*[[1977]] &amp;ndash; [[Sepp Herberger]], German football coach (b. 1897)
*[[1982]] &amp;ndash; [[Archibald MacLeish]], American poet and [[Librarian of Congress]] (b. 1892)
*[[1986]] &amp;ndash; [[Sibte Hassan]], Pakistani activist, journalist and writer (b. 1916)
*[[1989]] &amp;ndash; [[Doru Davidovici]], Romanian writer and fighter pilot (b. 1945)
*[[1991]] &amp;ndash; [[Steve Marriott]], British singer and songwriter ([[Small Faces|The Small Faces]]) ([[Humble Pie (band)|Humble Pie]]) (b. 1947)
*  1991   &amp;ndash; [[Don Siegel]], American film director (b. 1912)
*[[1992]] &amp;ndash; [[Benny Hill]], British comedian (b. 1924)
*[[1993]] &amp;ndash; [[Cantinflas]], Mexican comedian and actor (b. 1911)
*[[1994]] &amp;ndash; [[Jean Carmet]], French actor (b. 1920)
*[[1996]] &amp;ndash; [[Christopher Robin Milne]], son of [[A.A. Milne]] (b. 1920)
*[[1999]] &amp;ndash; [[Rick Rude]], American professional wrestler (b. 1958)
*  1999   &amp;ndash; [[Señor Wences]], Spanish ventriloquist and comedian (b. 1896)
*  1999   &amp;ndash; [[Eric David Harris]], perpetrator of the Columbine High massacre (b. 1981)
*  1999   &amp;ndash; [[Dylan Klebold]], perpetrator of the Columbine High massacre (b. 1981)
*  1999   &amp;ndash; [[Cassie Bernall]], [[Columbine High School massacre]] victim (b. 1981)
*  1999   &amp;ndash; [[Rachel Joy Scott]], Columbine High School massacre victim (b. 1981)
*[[2001]] &amp;ndash; [[Giuseppe Sinopoli]], Italian conductor and composer (b. 1946)
*[[2002]] &amp;ndash; [[Alan Dale (singer)|Alan Dale]], American singer (b. 1925)
*[[2003]] &amp;ndash; [[Ruth Hale (playwright and actress)|Ruth Hale]], American playwright and actress (b. 1908)
*  2003   &amp;ndash; [[Daijiro Kato]], Japanese motorcycle racer (b. 1976)
*  2003   &amp;ndash; [[Bernard Katz]], German-born biophysicist, recipient of the [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine]] (b. 1911)
*[[2005]] &amp;ndash; [[Fumio Niwa]], Japanese novelist (b. 1904)
*  2005   &amp;ndash; [[Zygfryd Blaut]], Polish football player (b. 1943)
*[[2007]] &amp;ndash; [[Andrew Hill]], American jazz composer and pianist (b. 1931)
*  2007   &amp;ndash; [[Michael Fu Tieshan]], Chinese bishop (b. 1931).
*  2007   &amp;ndash; [[Fred Fish]], a computer programmer on the [[GNU Debugger]] and &quot;Fish disks&quot; (b. 1952)
*[[2008]] &amp;ndash; [[VL Mike]], American rapper (b. 1976)
*  2008   &amp;ndash; [[Monica Lovinescu]], Romanian essayist, literary critic and journalist (b. 1923)
*[[2009]] &amp;ndash; [[Beata Asimakopoulou]], Greek actress (b. 1932)
*[[2010]] &amp;ndash; [[Dorothy Height]], American civil rights activist (b. 1912)

