====Ligatures====
[[Unicode]] primary range for basic Arabic language alphabet is the U+06xx range. Other ranges are for compatibility to older standards and do contain some ligatures. The only compulsory [[Typographical ligature|ligature]] for fonts and text processing in the basic Arabic language alphabet range U+06xx are ones for ''{{transl|ar|DIN|lām}}'' + ''{{transl|ar|DIN|ʾalif}}''. All other ligatures (''{{transl|ar|DIN|yāʾ}}'' + ''{{transl|ar|DIN|mīm}}'', etc.) are optional. Example to illustrate it is below. The exact outcome may depend on your browser and font configuration.
* (initial or isolated) ''{{transl|ar|DIN|lām}}'' + ''{{transl|ar|DIN|ʾalif}}'' (''{{transl|ar|DIN|lā}}'' {{IPA|/laː/}}):
:: &lt;span style=&quot;line-height:180%;padding:10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;5&quot;&gt;{{rtl-lang|ar|لا}}&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
Note: [[Unicode]] also has in its Presentation Form B FExx range a code for this ligature. If your browser and font are configured right for Arabic, the ligature displayed above should be identical to this one, U+FEFB ARABIC LIGATURE LAM WITH ALEF ISOLATED FORM:
:: &lt;span style=&quot;line-height:180%;padding:10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;5&quot;&gt;{{rtl-lang|ar|ﻻ}}&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

* (final or medial) ''{{transl|ar|DIN|lām}}'' + ''{{transl|ar|DIN|ʾalif}}'' (''{{transl|ar|DIN|lā}}'' {{IPA|/laː/}}):
:: &lt;span style=&quot;line-height:180%;padding:10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;5&quot;&gt;{{rtl-lang|ar|ـلا}}&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
Note: [[Unicode]] also has in its Presentation Form B U+FExx range a code for this ligature. If your browser and font are configured right for Arabic, the ligature displayed above should be identical to this one, U+FEFC ARABIC LIGATURE LAM WITH ALEF FINAL FORM:
:: &lt;span style=&quot;line-height:180%;padding:10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;5&quot;&gt;{{rtl-lang|ar|ـﻼ}}&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

Another interesting ligature in the [[Unicode]] Presentation Form A range U+FB50 to U+FDxx is the special code for glyph for the ligature ''{{transl|ar|DIN|Allāh}}'' (“God”), U+FDF2 ARABIC LIGATURE ALLAH ISOLATED FORM:
:: &lt;span style=&quot;line-height:180%;padding:10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;5&quot;&gt;{{rtl-lang|ar|ﷲ}}&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

This latter ligature code again is a work-around for the shortcomings of most text processors, which are incapable of displaying the correct [[harakat|vowel marks]] for the word ''{{transl|ar|DIN|[[Allāh]]}}'' in [[Koran]]. Because Arabic script is used to write other texts rather than Koran only, rending ''{{transl|ar|DIN|lām}}'' + ''{{transl|ar|DIN|lām}}'' + ''{{transl|ar|DIN|hāʾ}}'' as the previous ligature is considered faulty:&lt;ref&gt;[[SIL International]]: [http://scripts.sil.org/cms/scripts/page.php?site_id=nrsi&amp;id=ArabicFonts&amp;_sc=1 This simplified style is often preferred for clarity, especially in non-Arabic languages]&lt;/ref&gt;
* ''{{transl|ar|DIN|lām}}'', (geminated) ''{{transl|ar|DIN|lām}}'' (with implied short ''a'' vowel, reversed) ''{{transl|ar|DIN|hāʾ}}'' :
:: &lt;span style=&quot;line-height:180%;padding:10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;5&quot;&gt;{{rtl-lang|ar|لله}}&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt; or &lt;span dir=&quot;rtl&quot; lang=&quot;ar&quot; style=&quot;font-family:mry_KacstQurn,'DejaVu Sans',Scheherazade; font-size:200%;line-height:180%&quot;&gt; لله &lt;/span&gt; &lt;small&gt;(if one of these fonts: ''mry_KacstQurn, DejaVu Sans'' or ''Scheherazade'' is installed, the latter would render without the gemination mark and superscript Alef)&lt;/small&gt;
* ''{{transl|ar|DIN|ʾalif}}'', ''{{transl|ar|DIN|lām}}'', (geminated) ''{{transl|ar|DIN|lām}}'' (with implied short ''{{transl|ar|DIN|a}}'' vowel, reversed) ''{{transl|ar|DIN|hāʾ}}'' :
:: &lt;span style=&quot;line-height:180%;padding:10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;5&quot;&gt;{{rtl-lang|ar|الله}}&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt; or &lt;span dir=&quot;rtl&quot; lang=&quot;ar&quot; style=&quot;font-family:mry_KacstQurn,'DejaVu Sans',Scheherazade; font-size:200%;line-height:180%&quot;&gt; الله &lt;/span&gt; &lt;small&gt;(if one of these fonts: ''mry_KacstQurn, DejaVu Sans'' or ''Scheherazade'' is installed, the latter would render without the gemination mark and superscript Alef)&lt;/small&gt;
* ''{{transl|ar|ʾalif}}'' + ''{{transl|ar|lām}}'' + (U+0651 ARABIC SHADDA) + (U+0670 ARABIC LETTER SUPERSCRIPT ALEF) + ''{{transl|ar|DIN|hāʾ}}'' :
:: &lt;span dir=&quot;rtl&quot; lang=&quot;ar&quot; style=&quot;font-family:mry_KacstQurn,Scheherazade; font-size:200%;line-height:200%&quot;&gt; اللّٰه &lt;/span&gt;

====Gemination====
{{further|[[Shadda]]}}
[[Image:00-Taschdid.svg|thumb|right|The ''{{transl|ar|DIN|šaddah}}'' ([[shadda]]) sign indicates a doubled consonant.]]

[[Gemination]] is the doubling of a consonant. Instead of writing the letter twice, Arabic places a ''W''-shaped sign called ''{{transl|ar|DIN|šaddah}}'', or ''shadda'', above it. (The generic term for such [[diacritic]]al signs is ''{{transl|ar|DIN|[[harakat|ḥarakāt]]}}''). When a shadda is used on a consonant which also takes a [[Harakat#Kasra|''{{transl|ar|DIN|kasrah}}'']] (a dash below the consonant indicating that it takes a short /i/ as its vowel), the kasra may be written between the consonant and the ''{{transl|ar|DIN|šaddah}}'' rather than in its normal place.

