==Further reading==
* {{cite book | last=Ely | first=Michael | authorlink=Michael Ely | title=Centauri Dawn | series=Sid Meier's Alpha Centauri, Book I | date=2000-11-28 | publisher=[[Pocket Books]] | location=[[New York City|New York, NY]], USA 10020 | isbn=978-0671040772}} - covers the early years of colonization of the planet Chiron and describes the siege of United Nations HQ by the Spartans, the loss of Peacekeeper sovereignty and the consequent flight by the United Nations survivors into Gaian territory.
* {{cite book | last=Ely | first=Michael | authorlink=Michael Ely | title=Dragon Sun | series=Sid Meier's Alpha Centauri, Book II | date=2001-08-28 | publisher=[[Pocket Books]] | location=[[New York City|New York, NY]], USA 10020 | isbn=978-0671040789}} - occurs years after the events of ''Centauri Dawn'' and describes the Gaia's Stepdaughters' use of &quot;mindworms&quot; to rebuff an attack by the technologically superior Morgan Industries.
* {{cite book | last=Ely | first=Michael | authorlink=Michael Ely | title=Twilight of the Mind | series=Sid Meier's Alpha Centauri, Book III | date=2002-01-29 |publisher=[[Pocket Books]] | location=[[New York City|New York, NY]], USA 10020 | isbn=978-0671040796}} - follows the tension between the University of Planet and the Lord's Believers and describes the use of [[weapons of mass destruction|singularity bombs]] to destroy Morgan Industries and the Spartan Federation and the native life uprising which destroys humanity.
&lt;!-- * {{cite book | last1= Hartpence | first1=Chris | title=Vel's SMAX Guide, version 4.0: The Unofficial Guide to Sid Meier's Alpha Centauri | url=http://www.weplayciv.com/forums/downloads.php?do=file&amp;id=7 | format = PDF | accessdate=2010-08-12 | date=2001-09-21 | publisher=BookSurge Publishing | location=Charleston, SC, USA | isbn=978-1588984906}} - 253 page self-published advance strategy guide covering both single player and multiplayer modes. --&gt;
* {{cite web | url=http://www.gamespot.com/features/alphac_gg/index.html?om_act=convert&amp;om_clk=gameguides&amp;tag=gameguide%3Btitle%3B1 | title=Sid Meier's Alpha Centauri Game Guide | first1=Chris | last1=Jenson | first2=Doug | last2=Radcliffe | first3=Elliot | last3=Chin | first4=Ethan (Design) | last4=O'Brien | date=1999-02-17 | work=[[Gamespot]] | publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] Inc | location=San Francisco, CA, USA 94105 | accessdate=2010-08-03 | ref=GameGuide}}
