Other distinct dialects include the [[Homshetsi]] language of the [[Hemshin people]] and [[Lomavren language]] of the [[Bosha (Roma)|Bosha]], both of which are categorized as belonging to the Armenian [[language family]].

{{ Armenian language | 1 | 2 | }}

===Standardized forms===
Armenian is a [[pluricentric language]], having two [[Standard language|standardized]] forms: [[Eastern Armenian]] and [[Western Armenian]].

===Historical Armenian dialects===
In 1909, linguist [[Hrachia Acharian]] in his &quot;Classification des dialects arméniens&quot; (&quot;Classification of Armenian dialects&quot;) surveyed many of the Armenian dialects in what is now present day [[Turkey]], [[Armenia]], [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]], [[Iran]], [[Azerbaijan]] and other surrounding countries settled by [[Armenians]]. Unlike the traditional dialect division of Armenian into western and eastern dialects, [[Hrachia Acharian|Acharian]] divided Armenian into three main dialects based on which indicative particles are used. He labeled them as the -owm dialects, gë dialects, and -el dialects. These three major dialects were further divided into sub-dialects.

====Eastern dialects====
;-owm Dialects:
* [[Yerevan]], [[Doğubeyazıt|Bayazet]], [[Tabriz]] (Kala and Lilava quarters), [[Gavar]]
* [[Tbilisi]] ([[Avlabari|Havlabar]] quarter)
* [[Shushi]], [[Ganja, Azerbaijan|Gandzak]] (Gyanja), [[Shaki, Azerbaijan|Shaki]], [[Baku]], [[Derbent]], [[Ağstafa|Aghstafa]], [[Dilijan]], [[Vanadzor]], [[Qazakh|Kazakh]], [[Lori]], [[Karadagh]] (Ardabil Province, Iran), [[Mujumbar]] (Kermān Province, Oran), [[Tabriz]] (Lilava quarter), [[Burdur]] (near İzmir, Turkey), [[Ödemiş|Yodemish]] (İzmir Province, Turkey)
* [[Şamaxı|Shamakhi]], [[Quba (city)|Kuba]]
* [[Astrakhan]]
* [[Julfa]], [[Isfahan]] ([[New Julfa]] quarter), [[Shiraz]], [[Hamadan]], [[Bushehr]], [[Tehran]], [[Qazvin]], [[Rasht]], [[Bandar-e Anzali]]
* [[Aşağı Əylis|Nerkin (Lower) Agulis]], [[Çənnəb|Tsagna]], [[Yuxarı Əylis|Verin (Upper) Agulis]], [[Yuxarı Əndəli|Verin (Upper) Handamej]], [[Danagyrt|Tanagirt]], [[Urmis|Urumis]], [[Dəstə|Dosti]], [[Kələki|Kyalaki]] (villages in [[Nakhichevan]])

;-el Dialects:
* [[Maragheh]]
* [[Khoy]], [[Maku, Iran|Maku]], [[Iğdır]], [[Kori]], [[Hartashen, Syunik|Alighuli]], [[Mughanjugh]], [[Karashen]], [[Alilu]], [[Angeghakot]], [[Ghushchi]], [[Ashotavan|Tazakend]], [[Uyts|Uz]], [[Mazra]], [[Balak]], [[Shaghat]], [[Ltsen]], [[Sisian]], [[Nerkin Kilisa]]
* [[Artvin]], [[Ardahan]], [[Ardanuç|Artanutch]], [[Oltu|Olti]]

====Western dialects====
;gë Dialects:
