| '''get''' &quot;river&quot; || '''water''' (&lt; [[Old English language|OE]] ''wæter'')|| '''utur'''&lt;ref name='Umbrian'/&gt; &quot;water&quot;|| '''hudōr''' &quot;water&quot;|| '''udan''' &quot;water&quot;|| '''{{PIE|(*wodor, *wedor, *uder-) from *wed-}}''' &quot;water&quot;
|-
| '''gorç'''&lt;ref name='ts'/&gt; &quot;work &quot; || '''work''' (&lt; [[Old English language|OE]] ''weorc'')|| '''urgēre''' &quot;push, drive&quot;|| '''ergon''' &quot;work&quot;|| '''varcas''' &quot;activity&quot;|| '''{{PIE|*werǵ-}}''' &quot;to work&quot;
|-
| '''meç'''&lt;ref name='ts'/&gt; &quot;great &quot; || '''much''' (&lt; [[Old English language|OE]] ''mycel &quot;great, big, many&quot;'')|| '''magnus''' &quot;great&quot;|| '''megas''' &quot;great, large&quot;|| '''mahant''' &quot;great&quot;|| '''{{PIE|*meǵ-}}''' &quot;great&quot;
|-
| '''ançanot''''&lt;ref name='ts'/&gt; &quot;stranger, unfamiliar&quot; || '''unknown''' (&lt; [[Old English language|OE]] ''uncnawen'')|| '''ignōtus''',&lt;ref name='not'&gt;The prefixes for &quot;not&quot; in Latin are &quot;in-&quot; and &quot;i-&quot;, and &quot;an-&quot; and &quot;a-&quot; in Greek and Sanskrit, which correspond to the PIE *n-.&lt;/ref&gt; '''ignōrāntem'''&lt;ref name='not'/&gt; &quot;unknown, ignorant&quot;|| '''agnōstos'''&lt;ref name='not'/&gt; &quot;unknown&quot;|| '''ajñāta'''&lt;ref name='not'/&gt; &quot;unfamiliar&quot; || '''{{PIE|*n- + *ǵneH₃-}}''' &quot;not&quot; + &quot;to know&quot;
|-
| '''meṙaç''' &quot;dead&quot; || '''murder''' (&lt; [[Old English language|OE]] ''morþor''&lt;ref name='þ'/&gt;)|| '''mortalis''' &quot;mortal&quot; || '''ambrotos''' &quot;immortal&quot;|| '''mṛta''' &quot;dead&quot; || '''{{PIE|*mrtro-, from (*mor-, *mr-)}}''' &quot;to die&quot;
